<subSubSection id="5409F7B10A0FE16152482A1535CEA315" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="typification">
<paragraph id="5E880EC1033D74FBD721F7A88CD3C231" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Typification.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EA77F1A3C0A54B1ABD1605FD27AEE860" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
This species has long been known as 
<taxonomicName id="F43F44A230AAE081145564871E24B87E" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tubata">
<emphasis id="8441603EE2F129A0C1EDCC7141215DA2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea tubata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but the name 
<taxonomicName id="0E81932331531DB73BC6944D3E2E069A" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sidifolia">
<emphasis id="57C40E8A0E69D016C6EED468A51FABDA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea sidifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was published in the same year and has precedence so should be adopted for this species. Both names were based on the same collection. In order to avoid ambiguity the specimen at GOET is here chosen as lectotype even though it is not annotated either by Schrader or by Nees. It is only extant example of the original material that we are aware of.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2D2CDB4C2750C542DC9F96158F71E59E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="75899CEC2ED11CF54FD840000CD2388F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="98412F5C8E9F20C09211A06A16576F05" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A very distinctive species because of its liana habit, hypocrateriform corolla, exserted stamens and tomentellous ovary and capsule. It is the only species we have observed in which the lower half of the style is pubescent.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
